tsp_tasks

Class TspData

  • java.lang.Object
    • tsp_tasks.TspData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TspData
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    TspData is a class designed to store the specific information in a TspReadyTask object. The way to deal with a TaskTsp object is decided by the args in it, which is a list of TspData objects.
    See Also:

    • Constructor Detail

      • TspData

        public TspData(double distance,
               java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> ORDERED,
               java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> UNORDERED)
        The class constructor initializing the fields.
        Parameters:
        distance - The distance of the tour, when the object is created, it can be set to a fixed value, say, -1 or -8. The field will be modified when the distance calculation is done.
        ORDERED - The order of the cities whose sequence is already decided. The first city in the list is where the tour starts.
        UNORDERED - The cities whose order has not been decided yet. The order of the elements in this list does not matter.
